<dl id="n41019d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41019d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41019d"> 19(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Michael Scott / asked devil to / make rope of / sand</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>Twisting ropes out of sand</mark> was a device by which <mark>Michael Scot baffled a devil</mark> for whom he had to find constant employment. <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RBTE3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE3"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) VII, 213</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
